# Callback Functions

Always extract callback functions passed to array methods (`.forEach`, `.map`, `.filter`, `.find`, `.reduce`, `.some`, `.every`, etc.) into a named `const` before passing them.

```javascript
// BAD — anonymous inline callback
this.IBANForm.forEach((field) => {
  field.value = '';
});

const field = this.IBANForm.find((f) => f.name === fieldName);

// GOOD — named const callback
const resetValue = (field) => {
  field.value = '';
};
this.IBANForm.forEach(resetValue);

const isMatchingField = (f) => f.name === fieldName;
const field = this.IBANForm.find(isMatchingField);
```

This applies to all higher-order function calls, not just array methods — e.g. `setTimeout`, `$watch`, `Promise.then`, etc.
